# 🏗️ MVC (Model-View-Controller) Pattern

SB Stocks is developed using the **Model-View-Controller (MVC)** architectural pattern. MVC divides the application into three independent components: **Model**, **View**, and **Controller**. This separation improves code organization, maintainability, scalability, and makes the application easier to develop and test.

---

## MVC Architecture

```
                User
                  │
                  ▼
        HTTP Request (API)
                  │
                  ▼
          View (Routes Layer)
                  │
                  ▼
      Controller (Business Logic)
                  │
                  ▼
      Model (Database Operations)
                  │
                  ▼
           MongoDB Database
                  │
                  ▼
      Controller Processes Data
                  │
                  ▼
         JSON Response to User
```

---

# 1. Model Layer

The **Model** layer is responsible for managing the application's data. It defines the database structure using **Mongoose schemas** and performs all database operations with MongoDB.

### Responsibilities
- Define database schemas.
- Store and retrieve application data.
- Validate data before saving.
- Perform CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.
- Maintain relationships between collections.

### Models Used
- **User Model**
  - Stores user details such as name, email, password, and profile information.

- **Portfolio Model**
  - Stores virtual portfolios and current stock holdings.

- **Transaction Model**
  - Records all buy and sell transactions.

- **Stock Model**
  - Stores stock information, symbols, prices, and market data.

---

# 2. Controller Layer

The **Controller** contains the business logic of the application. It receives requests from the routes, validates the input, communicates with the models, and sends appropriate responses.

### Responsibilities
- Process client requests.
- Validate user input.
- Authenticate users.
- Execute trading operations.
- Update portfolio balances.
- Calculate profits and losses.
- Retrieve stock information.
- Handle application errors.
- Return API responses.

### Example Controller Functions
- Register User
- Login User
- Get Stock List
- Buy Stock
- Sell Stock
- Create Portfolio
- View Portfolio
- View Transaction History

---

# 3. View Layer (Routes)

In SB Stocks, the **View** is implemented through REST API routes. These routes define how the application responds to different HTTP requests.

### Responsibilities
- Receive HTTP requests.
- Map requests to controller functions.
- Return JSON responses.
- Define API endpoints.
- Handle request parameters.

### Example API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|----------|-----------------|----------------------------|
| POST | /register | Register a new user |
| POST | /login | User login |
| GET | /stocks | Fetch stock listings |
| GET | /portfolio | Retrieve portfolio details |
| POST | /buy | Buy stocks |
| POST | /sell | Sell stocks |
| GET | /transactions | View transaction history |

